TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
The vertex of the parabola defined by
\[f(x) = x^2+4x\]
is the point 
$BR
(  \{ ans_rule(5) \},
EOT

ANS(num_cmp(-2));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
 \{ ans_rule(5) \} ).
EOT

ANS(num_cmp(-4));


SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT')); 
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD  We have
\[f(x) = x^2+4x+4 = (x+2)^2-4\]
and so the vertex is the point \((-2,-4)\).
EOT






